    "# 4.10.3\n",
    "Write the code that generates a normal sample with given μ and σ , and thecode that calculates m and s from the sample. Do the same using the Bayes’estimator assuming a prior distribution for μ."

    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from scipy.stats import norm\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",

    "def Generate_Random_Normal_Unif(N, mu, sigma):\n",
    "    rand = []\n",
    "    for i in range(400):\n",
    "        tmpRand = sum(np.random.uniform(0,1,6))-3\n",
    "        rand.append(tmpRand*sigma+mu)\n",
    "    return rand"

    "# 4.10.6\n",
    "For a two-class problem, generate normal samples for two classes with diﬀer-ent variances, then use parametric classiﬁcation to estimate the discriminantpoints. Compare these with the theoretical values."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 24,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def Calculate_likelihood_Posterior_EqPriors(mu1, sigma1, mu2, simga2):\n",
    "    ox = []\n",
    "    oy1 = []\n",
    "    oy2 = []\n",
    "    py1 = []\n",
    "    py2 = []\n",
    "    for i in range(0,12):\n",
    "        x=i/2\n",
    "        ox.append(x)\n",
    "        oy1.append(norm.pdf(x,mu1,sigma1))      # likelihoods\n",
    "        oy2.append(norm.pdf(x,mu2,sigma2))\n",
    "        py1.append(oy1[i]/(oy1[i]+oy2[i]))      # posteriors\n",
    "        py2.append(oy2[i]/(oy1[i]+oy2[i]))  \n",
    "    return ox, oy1, py1, oy2, py2"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 25,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def Calculate_Intersections(mu1, sigma1, mu2, sigma2):\n",
    "    a=1/(2*sigma2*sigma2)-1/(2*sigma1*sigma1)\n",
    "    b=mu1/(sigma1*sigma1)-mu2/(sigma2*sigma2)\n",
    "    c=(mu2*mu2)/(2*sigma2*sigma2)-(mu1*mu1)/(2*sigma1*sigma1)+ np.log(sigma2/sigma1)\n",
    "    xrt1=(-b+np.sqrt(b*b-4*a*c))/(2*a)\n",
    "    xrt2=(-b-np.sqrt(b*b-4*a*c))/(2*a)\n",
    "    return xrt1, xrt2"
   ]
  },

   "metadata": {},

   "source": [
    "mu1,sigma1=3,1;     # unknown parameters\n",
    "mu2, sigma2=2, 0.3;\n",
    "# equal priors\n",
    "ox, oy1, py1, oy2, py2 = Calculate_likelihood_Posterior_EqPriors(mu1, sigma1, mu2, sigma2)\n",
    "plt.plot(ox,oy1,'-') \n",
    "plt.plot(ox,oy2,'-')\n",
    "plt.plot(ox,py1,'-') \n",
    "plt.plot(ox,py2,'-')\n",
    "plt.show()"

    "def get_Discriminant(x, mu, s):\n",
    "    # Constant values only moove the function through the y axis so -1/2*np.log(2*np.pi) can be ignored.\n",
    "    return (-np.log(s)-(x-mu)**2/(2*s**2))\n",
    "\n",
    "ox = [x * 0.01 for x in range(0, 600)]\n",
    "dy1 = get_Discriminant(np.array(ox), mu1, sigma1)\n",
    "dy2 = get_Discriminant(np.array(ox), mu2, sigma2)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(ox,dy1,'-') \n",
    "plt.plot(ox,dy2,'-')\n",
    "\n",
    "signs_check = dy1-dy2\n",
    "zero_crossings = np.where(np.diff(np.sign(signs_check)))[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "print([ox[i] for i in zero_crossings])"
   ]

    "from enum import Enum\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "class NodeState(Enum):\n",
    "    READY = 1\n",
    "    VISITING = 2\n",
    "    SUCCESS = 3\n",
    "    FAILED = 4\n",
    "    RUNNING = 5\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "class Node:\n",
    "    def __init__(self, action):\n",
    "        self.state = NodeState.READY\n",
    "        self.action = action\n",
    "\n",
    "    def execute(self):\n",
    "        self.state = NodeState.RUNNING\n",
    "        result = self.action\n",
    "        if result:\n",
    "            self.state = NodeState.SUCCESS\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            self.state = NodeState.FAILED\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "class Sequence(Node):\n",
    "    def __init__(self, children):\n",
    "        self.state = NodeState.READY\n",
    "        self.children = children\n",
    "\n",
    "    def execute(self):\n",
    "        self.state = NodeState.RUNNING\n",
    "        for node in self.children:\n",
    "            node.execute()\n",
    "            if node.state == NodeState.FAILED:\n",
    "                self.state = NodeState.FAILED\n",
    "                return\n",
    "        self.state = NodeState.SUCCESS\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "class Selector(Node):\n",
    "    def __init__(self, children):\n",
    "        self.state = NodeState.READY\n",
    "        self.children = children\n",
    "\n",
    "    def execute(self):\n",
    "        self.state = NodeState.RUNNING\n",
    "        for node in self.children:\n",
    "            node.execute()\n",
    "            if node.state == NodeState.SUCCESS:\n",
    "                self.state = NodeState.SUCCESS\n",
    "                return\n",
    "        self.state = NodeState.FAILED"
   ]

    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from scipy.stats import multivariate_normal\n",
    "from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import Axes3D\n",
    "\n",
    "#Parameters to set\n",
    "mu_x = 0\n",
    "variance_x = 3\n",
    "\n",
    "mu_y = 0\n",
    "variance_y = 15\n",
    "\n",
    "mu_x1 = 0\n",
    "variance_x1 = 15\n",
    "\n",
    "mu_y1 = 0\n",
    "variance_y1 = 20\n",
    "\n",
    "#Create grid and multivariate normal\n",
    "x = np.linspace(-10,10,500)\n",
    "y = np.linspace(-10,10,500)\n",
    "X, Y = np.meshgrid(x,y)\n",
    "pos = np.empty(X.shape + (2,))\n",
    "pos[:, :, 0] = X; pos[:, :, 1] = Y\n",
    "rv = multivariate_normal([mu_x, mu_y], [[variance_x, 0], [0, variance_y]])\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "rv1 = multivariate_normal([mu_x1, mu_y1], [[variance_x1, 0], [0, variance_y1]])\n",
    "\n",
    "#Make a 3D plot\n",
    "fig = plt.figure()\n",
    "ax = fig.gca(projection='3d')\n",
    "ax.plot_surface(X, Y, rv.pdf(pos),cmap='viridis',linewidth=0)\n",
    "ax.plot_surface(X, Y, rv1.pdf(pos),cmap='viridis',linewidth=0)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('X axis')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Y axis')\n",
    "ax.set_zlabel('Z axis')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
